For the pork, heat the oil in a frying pan. Add the pork and cook for five minutes on each side, until cooked through.For the creamed leeks, melt the butter in a hot pan. Add the leeks and chard and saut√© for three minutes.Add the double cream and sage, warm through and season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper.To serve, place the creamed leeks onto the centre of a warmed plate and top with the pork. Arrange the new potatoes around the plate.